cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic relation extraction and classification in scientific papers, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as an end-to-end relation extraction model, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in information retrieval, suggesting it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which are commonly used in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
